org.rsna.ctp.stdstages.database

Class DatabaseAdapter

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.rsna.ctp.stdstages.database.DatabaseAdapter
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    TciaXnatDatabaseAdapter, TestDatabaseAdapter

    public class DatabaseAdapter
extends java.lang.Object
    An adapter for accessing an external database. Classes extending this class can be accessed by the CTP DatabaseExportService, which passes objects received from the pipeline to it for processing.

    • Method Detail

      • setID

        public void setID(int n)
        Set an ID string for this DatabaseAdapter.

      • reset

        public Status reset()
        Reset the database interface. This method is called by the DatabaseExportService if it is restarted.

      • connect

        public Status connect()
        Establish a connection to the database. This method is called by the DatabaseExportService when it is about to call methods in the database interface. This call can be used by the database interface to, for example, connect to a relational database.

      • disconnect

        public Status disconnect()
        Disconnect from the database. This method is called by the DatabaseExportService when it is temporarily finished with the database. This call can be used by the database interface to, for example, disconnect from a relational database.

      • shutdown

        public Status shutdown()
        Stop the database interface. This method is called by the DatabaseExportService when it is about to shut down. This call notifies the database interface that no further accesses will occur. The database interface should not rely on this call for anything critical since external conditions may prevent the call from occurring.

      • process

        public Status process(DicomObject dicomObject,
             java.io.File storedFile,
             java.lang.String url)
        Process a DICOM object. This method is called by the DatabaseExportService when it receives a DICOM file.
        Parameters:
        dicomObject - The DicomObject to be processed. This object points to a transient file in the queue.
        storedFile - The File pointing to the object stored in the FileStorageService, or null if the object has not been stored.
        url - The URL pointing to the stored object or null if no URL is available.

      • uidQuery

        public java.util.Map<java.lang.String,UIDResult> uidQuery(java.util.Set<java.lang.String> uidSet)
        Query the database to determine whether it has received information for any of a set of instance UIDs. This method is called by the DatabaseExportService's query servlet when it receives a request to verify that objects which were submitted have been processed.
        Parameters:
        uidSet - The set of UIDs to be searched. Each UID is an instance UID (which, for a DicomObject, means SOPInstanceUID).
        Returns:
        a Map containing all the UIDs in the uidSet as keys, and UIDResult objects indicating whether the referenced objects have been processed. If the database does not support queries for object presence or absence, return null.
